This paper is focused on the development and comparison of predictive models for readmission after heart failure hospitalization using administrative claims data. The use of neural network-based models and logistic regression for prediction suggests a focus on machine learning and data analysis, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the examination of patients' hospitalization timelines on prediction performance suggests a focus on data analysis and modeling, which could also fall under the categories of cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction and Computer-Supported Cooperative Work). The use of neural networks and deep learning approaches also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the use of logistic regression and statistical modeling suggests a focus on computational statistics, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Computational Statistics).
